docs.abstract: After “The Handmaid’s Tale” made it a player, Hulu has another ambitious show in “The Looming Tower.” But merger mania makes for a murky future.
docs.snippet: After “The Handmaid’s Tale” made it a player, Hulu has another ambitious show in “The Looming Tower.” But merger mania makes for a murky future.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lawrence Wright was reluctant to adapt “The Looming Tower,” his Pulitzer Prize-winning history of Al Qaeda and the run-up to 9/11. But it wasn’t lost on him that the number of deals for scripted series was rapidly increasing each year — a development that went along with the sudden rise of the streaming industry.

headline.main: Hulu Puts Up a Fight Against Netflix, Amazon and Apple
headline.print_headline: Hulu Makes Play to Contend With Netflix and Amazon

docs.abstract: While doctors say passengers’ greatest health risk may be from fellow travelers, there is some risk if surfaces in cabins and bathrooms are not adequately cleaned.

docs.lead_paragraph: Is there anything air travelers despise more than a flight delay? Perhaps sitting in a dirty airplane or next to someone who is coughing, sneezing or worse.

docs.abstract: The Advertising Research Foundation, which gave an award to the research firm last year for its work with data, now says advertisers need to consider the ethics of how consumer data is collected and used.

docs.lead_paragraph: An advertising trade group that gave an award to Cambridge Analytica last year for its “big data” work during the 2016 presidential election is now urging marketers to reconsider the ethics of how consumer information is collected and used.

docs.abstract: The island nation has started to put in place a new law requiring companies with 25 employees or more to show that they pay men and women equally.
docs.snippet: The island nation has started to put in place a new law requiring companies with 25 employees or more to show that they pay men and women equally.
docs.lead_paragraph: REYKJAVIK, Iceland — Iceland this week began putting in place a new law that requires companies and government agencies to prove they are paying men and women equally, positioning the country at the forefront of global efforts to minimize gender inequality.

headline.main: Iceland Makes Companies Prove They’re Not Paying Women Less
headline.print_headline: Equal Pay Law Taking Effect in Iceland

docs.abstract: The founder of SoftBank, Masayoshi Son, is one of the world’s leading tech investors. He has pushed for Sprint, perhaps his marquee American investment, to merge with T-Mobile.
docs.snippet: The founder of SoftBank, Masayoshi Son, is one of the world’s leading tech investors. He has pushed for Sprint, perhaps his marquee American investment, to merge with T-Mobile.
docs.lead_paragraph: In an era of increasing foreign investment in the United States, few have been as acquisitive — or disruptive — as Masayoshi Son, the billionaire Japanese founder of SoftBank.

headline.main: T-Mobile-Sprint Merger Would Give Japan’s SoftBank Bigger Foothold in U.S.

docs.abstract: The mania over cryptocurrencies has gotten the attention of regulators. But currently, the S.E.C. and C.F.T.C. can only look on at what is happening.

docs.lead_paragraph: Cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and Ether have seeped into the public consciousness. Colleges including Duke and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology are offering classes in the blockchain technology that undergirds these virtual currencies to crowds of eager students.
